  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is a citation I got toward the end of my army career.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is called Army Commendation Ribbon.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it is based on three letters of commendation of general officers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then you were eligible for the Army Commendation Ribbon.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it specifies in detail what I did during the prisoner of war program.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it is signed by Major General Eddy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This is a wonderful family picture of my children and my grandchildren, at least two of my grandchildren, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] taken on the 15th of September during the celebration of our 50th wedding anniversary in Deerfield in our garden at 1010 Sunset Court.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Starting to the left is my daughter-in-law Bonnie, next to her, her husband, my-- our son, Daniel Shurman, next to her, our daughter Beverly Schurman-Lavitt, next to her, my son-in-law Dr.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Alan Lavitt.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In front to the left is my granddaughter Amanda Lavitt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Next to her is her grandmother, Margie Shurman.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Next to her is her grandfather Frank Shurman.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And next to him is my grandson Adam Shurman-Lavitt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1995, In September.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is my granddaughter Deborah Shurman, living in Pasadena, California, the daughter of my son Daniel Shurman.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is my family.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After a long day of introspection, we come to this end, which we call [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And next to me is my wife of 50 years, Margery.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Behind me is my son-in-law Alan Lavitt, and our granddaughter Amanda Lavitt, and our grandson Adam Schurmann-Lavitt.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Schurmann is spelled S-C-H-U-R-M-A-N-N, like I used to spell it, at the request of my beloved daughter Beverly.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that is Beverly Lavitt, also known as Beverley Schurmann-Lavitt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One of the things I'd say that has been the most important thing I've learned from my father's experience has been the importance of developing one's own strength and self-sufficiency.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't know why I'm crying, but it's a very important moment.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SOBS] I'm glad to be here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SOBS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I think one of the things that I find most remarkable about my husband's experience is his ability then and since to differentiate between the Nazis, who were the perpetrators, and the Germans, who had a long, proud history, and went through the valley along with their victims, at least retrospectively.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We go back to Germany often, because my husband has been able to maintain friendships that were deep and meaningful friendships.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And to not be bitter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And to not be bitter, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
